The Director General, National Centre for Women Development (NCWD), Mrs Mary Ekpere-Eta, has called for support for women to take their rightful place in the scheme of things across the nations. Mrs Ekpere- Eta, while speaking at a conference to celebrate the 2019 International Women’s Day (IWD) with the theme, Think Equal, Build fast and Innovate for change #BalanceForBetter, yesterday, in Abuja said government at all levels and across party lines should give women more opportunities in appointive positions to enable them to contribute their quota to nation building. She said as gender research, training and documentation center, their doors are open to more partners interested in working with them to advance the Nigeria gender agenda thereby urging everyone to avail themselves the opportunities in bridging the gap and empowering Nigerian women. Women’ll be adequately represented in my administration - Buhari Minister calls for women mentorship FG launches National Gender Plan for agriculture